[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = TheNumberLine\n\nusing PlutoUI\n\nmacro bind(def, element) # hide\n    quote\n        local iv = try Base.loaded_modules[Base.PkgId(Base.UUID(\"6e696c72-6542-2067-7265-42206c756150\"), \"AbstractPlutoDingetjes\")].Bonds.initial_value catch; b -> missing; end\n        local el = $(esc(element))\n        global $(esc(def)) = Core.applicable(Base.get, el) ? Base.get(el) : iv(el)\n        el\n    end\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"#TheNumberLine.jl","page":"Home","title":"TheNumberLine.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The Number Line is a common teaching tool in e.g. K-12 math classes accross the U.S.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Authors: Gael Forget and Jane Chapin","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: DOI)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"warning: Warning\nThis package is in early development stage when breaking changes are to be expected.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Use-Example","page":"Home","title":"Use Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In your web-browser (see User Directions for detail) :","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"type a number in the text box\nclick on the add button\nrepeat or reset","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Repeat a few times, e.g. with other numbers, to obtain something like the image shown below on the right hand side. You can also hit start over at any point (left hand side image).","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Start Add\n(Image: reset) (Image: reset)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Exercises","page":"Home","title":"Exercises","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Random-Turtle","page":"Home","title":"Random Turtle","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In the random turtle activity we take a series of N consecutive, random, steps on the number line. Each step is either -1 (left) or +1 (right) based on a coin flip. We do this N times in a row (10 times for example) and observe our final value at the end (green arrow). All you need to do this is copy the following line to a new code cell and run it:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"NumberLinePlot(rand((-1,1),10))","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: )","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The activity basically is do this a bunch of times and discuss how results can vary .","category":"page"},{"location":"#Histograms","page":"Home","title":"Histograms","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This module provides a simple way to create an empty histogram that students can print and write over.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"#using TheNumberLine\nimport TheNumberLine.histogram_template: make_hist, save_hist\n\nfig=make_hist()\nsave_hist(fig,file=\"hist.png\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: )","category":"page"},{"location":"#Various","page":"Home","title":"Various","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#.-Use-a-Slider","page":"Home","title":"1. Use a Slider","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In the first code cell of standard_number_line.jl, where values are entered, you can use a list of a slider or multiple choice instead.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To do this, replace the line that says","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"` Type value : ` $(@bind b html\"<input type=text>\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"with","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"`Select value of x from the list : ` $(@bind b Select([\"4\",\"3\",\"2\",\"1\",\"0\",\"-1\",\"-2\",\"-3\",\"-4\"],default=\"0\"))","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"or","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"`Choose value of x using slider : ` $(@bind b aSlider(-10:10; default=0))","category":"page"},{"location":"#.-Integers-Only","page":"Home","title":"2. Integers Only","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To restrict the number line to using integers (as opposed to reals), try changing TestType in standard_number_line.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To do this, replace the line that says","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"TestType=Number; NumberLineType=Float64; \"Number LineType = $(NumberLineType)\"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"with ","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"TestType=Int; NumberLineType=Int; \"NumberLineType = $(NumberLineType)\"","category":"page"},{"location":"#Main-Functions","page":"Home","title":"Main Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"NumberLinePlot\nNumberLineExpression\nhistogram_template.make_hist","category":"page"},{"location":"#TheNumberLine.NumberLinePlot","page":"Home","title":"TheNumberLine.NumberLinePlot","text":"NumberLinePlot(x)\n\nDisplay the number line sequence of operations, defined by vector x, as a graph.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#TheNumberLine.NumberLineExpression","page":"Home","title":"TheNumberLine.NumberLineExpression","text":"NumberLineExpression(x)\n\nDisplay the number line sequence of operations, defined by vector x, as text.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#TheNumberLine.histogram_template.make_hist","page":"Home","title":"TheNumberLine.histogram_template.make_hist","text":"make_hist()\n\nusing TheNumberLine\nimport TheNumberLine.histogram_template: make_hist, save_hist\n\nfig=make_hist()\nsave_hist(fig)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#User-Directions","page":"Home","title":"User Directions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You can try TheNumberLine.jl in the cloud without having to install anything.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: Dev)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"If instead you want to use TheNumberLine.jl then proceed as follows.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Download TheNumberLine.jl\nOpen a terminal window go to the TheNumberLine.jl/src/ folder\nStart Pluto.jl e.g. via julia -e \"using Pluto; Pluto.run()\"\nIn web browser window, select and open standard_number_line.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"tip: Tip\nSome tips for new users are provided below.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To use TheNumberLine.jl on your own computer, you'll need to download Julia itself beforehand.\nto close the session you want to go back to the terminal window and Press Ctrl+C","category":"page"}]
